    "Id": "chassisdef_urbanmech_UM-R63-CF_crossfire",
    "Name": "UrbanMech",
    "Details": "James’ Crossfire UrbanMech defies expectations by emphasizing surprise in combat. While opponents see UrbanMechs as slow and weak, the Crossfire reaches speeds up to 97 kph and can jump 180 meters, tripling typical mobility. Powered by a 180 XL engine and extra jump jets, it uses lightweight Ferro Fibrous armor and double heat sinks to support its weapons. Its armament includes four medium lasers, paired SRM-2 launchers with ammo, and a small laser. This simple, reliable loadout has defeated heavier foes, benefiting from low costs and easy replacement parts, ideal for the mobile Rockers.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: 360° Torso Twist</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.01</color></b>\n\n<color=#FFEF00>Arm Actuator Limits: Left Upper, Right Upper</color>\n\n<b><color=#0064e6>Used with permission from Aries Games and Miniatures.</color></b>",
